social_posts.post_text: Earth people, specifically Bostonians! A cool sci fi program from @thecoolidge is coming in January with a new limited silk screened poster by me. Two spacey color combos to choose from, very collectible! Get them in January at the Coolidge, or from me, I’ll have just 20 to sell. #spaceistheplace #sunra

Big ol’ full page in @globeandmail this weekend to go with their year-end quiz. Looks much better in print! 
Thanks @bryangeedesign

Update: SOLD
I’ve had this 2010 drawing of James Brown up for a few years, but ready to make way for new art now. Any locals interested in picking up for a low price? Framed, 17”x23”. Inks and dyes on watercolour paper.

Have been watching White Lotus - fun to try likenesses after getting into a show. Done on paper. 
#whitelotusseason2 #whitelotus

New silk screened posters from @kidicarus_store for @thecoolidge ‘s Art House Sci Fi series this month! 18x24, just 100 of them. You can get them in person at the theatre, or I’m willing to ship the few I have - one red/blue left and 6 green/magenta. They are US$30, DM if you want one!
Art for a big feature in @nymag this week - Inside Twitter during Elon’s takeover. Fun collaboration with @tomalberty, thank you!

#figuredrawing from this week, 10 and 5 minute poses with Dr. Martin’s dyes

#lifedrawing #drawingfromlife #figurativedrawing

#figuredrawing from last night. I had stopped using Dr. Marten’s dyes a long time ago because they fade over time, but the flow and brightness is pretty fun. 5, 10 and 15 min poses. 

#lifedrawing #fashionillustration #drawingfromlife #lifemodel

Was asked the other day by the @globeandmail to create a cartoon in response to a headline from this week for a new feature (in tomorrow’s paper). I found members of US congress wearing AR-15 pins to work particularly ghoulish, so here’s a ghoul, with a nod to Ruben’s Massacre of the Innocents. 
Illustrators, you should pitch timely ideas to AD @bryangeedesign !

Fun costumed life drawing session with quick poses. The complexity was in insanely hard to capture! Good practice. 

#figuredrawing #drawingfromlife #figuredrawings

NBA’s Generation War, for @gq. Originally a double page spread in the magazine but bumped to online (posted today). Done by hand, in layers and assembled in photoshop. Fun collaboration with AD @michael_houtz

In 2015 I worked on a series with @batman’s boss @zdarsky called Kaptara and never finished it. (My fault) 
But here we are in ‘23, it’s 98% done and 6 new(!) issues are coming out starting at the end of the month through @imagecomics. It’s a weird story with musclemen and wizards. Chip has posted volume one on his substack today. 
#imagecomics #kaptara

🚨 Event Alert - I’ll be at @fanexpocanada next weekend with @kirbyscomicart at table P33! It’s been more than 10 years since I’ve been there. Feeling rusty, I painted (acryl-gouache) a few random fan art samples today - which are for sale. You can get in touch with @kirbyscomicart to buy, whether you’re heading to the show or not. Or to commission something original!
More to come. 
PS: when I run out of ideas I always draw Green Goblin

I managed to do some #spookyseason #screamqueen paintings this month as I wade into the collector’s market with @kirbyscomicart, who is now selling my originals (other work on their site already). This one is Laurie Strode from Halloween, 10x15 in acryl-gouache on illustration board. I’m not sure how these will be priced but contact Kirby if interested, it’s definitely for sale!
